</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[264,1324,1103,1249]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dai &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2006" box="[619,767,1143,1168]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Bambusana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="multidentata">
<emphasis box="[619,767,1143,1168]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">multidentata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but can be separated from the latter by crown with a brown transverse band, the pygofer side having a long ventro­caudal process, and the style with the lateral lobe weakly developed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
